### DFS Traversal Orders (Trees)
- **Preorder**: Root → Left → Right (used for serialization)
- **Inorder**: Left → Root → Right (gives sorted order for BST)
- **Postorder**: Left → Right → Root (used for deletion)

### Common Mistakes
- Forgetting to mark nodes as visited (infinite loops in graphs)
- Stack overflow on deep recursion (use iterative DFS for large inputs)
- Not restoring state when backtracking

### Interview Tip
"I use DFS when I need to explore all paths or when the problem has a recursive structure. For shortest path, I switch to BFS."
